27 // -------------------------------------------------------------------
28 // Implementation of the Irregexp regular expression engine.
29 //
30 // The Irregexp regular expression engine is intended to be a complete
31 // implementation of ECMAScript regular expressions. It generates either
32 // bytecodes or native code.
33 
34 // The Irregexp regexp engine is structured in three steps.
35 // 1) The parser generates an abstract syntax tree. See ast.cc.
36 // 2) From the AST a node network is created. The nodes are all
37 // subclasses of RegExpNode. The nodes represent states when
38 // executing a regular expression. Several optimizations are
39 // performed on the node network.
40 // 3) From the nodes we generate either byte codes or native code
41 // that can actually execute the regular expression (perform
42 // the search). The code generation step is described in more
43 // detail below.
44 
45 // Code generation.
46 //
47 // The nodes are divided into four main categories.
48 // * Choice nodes
49 // These represent places where the regular expression can
50 // match in more than one way. For example on entry to an
51 // alternation (foo|bar) or a repetition (*, +, ? or {}).
52 // * Action nodes
53 // These represent places where some action should be
54 // performed. Examples include recording the current position
55 // in the input string to a register (in order to implement
56 // captures) or other actions on register for example in order
57 // to implement the counters needed for {} repetitions.
58 // * Matching nodes
59 // These attempt to match some element part of the input string.
60 // Examples of elements include character classes, plain strings
61 // or back references.
62 // * End nodes
63 // These are used to implement the actions required on finding
64 // a successful match or failing to find a match.
65 //
66 // The code generated (whether as byte codes or native code) maintains
67 // some state as it runs. This consists of the following elements:
68 //
69 // * The capture registers. Used for string captures.
70 // * Other registers. Used for counters etc.
71 // * The current position.
72 // * The stack of backtracking information. Used when a matching node
73 // fails to find a match and needs to try an alternative.
74 //
75 // Conceptual regular expression execution model:
76 //
77 // There is a simple conceptual model of regular expression execution
78 // which will be presented first. The actual code generated is a more
79 // efficient simulation of the simple conceptual model:
80 //
81 // * Choice nodes are implemented as follows:
82 // For each choice except the last {
83 // push current position
84 // push backtrack code location
85 // <generate code to test for choice>
86 // backtrack code location:
87 // pop current position
88 // }
89 // <generate code to test for last choice>
90 //
91 // * Actions nodes are generated as follows
92 // <push affected registers on backtrack stack>
93 // <generate code to perform action>
94 // push backtrack code location
95 // <generate code to test for following nodes>
96 // backtrack code location:
97 // <pop affected registers to restore their state>
98 // <pop backtrack location from stack and go to it>
99 //
100 // * Matching nodes are generated as follows:
101 // if input string matches at current position
102 // update current position
103 // <generate code to test for following nodes>
104 // else
105 // <pop backtrack location from stack and go to it>
106 //
107 // Thus it can be seen that the current position is saved and restored
108 // by the choice nodes, whereas the registers are saved and restored by
109 // by the action nodes that manipulate them.
110 //
111 // The other interesting aspect of this model is that nodes are generated
112 // at the point where they are needed by a recursive call to Emit(). If
113 // the node has already been code generated then the Emit() call will
114 // generate a jump to the previously generated code instead. In order to
115 // limit recursion it is possible for the Emit() function to put the node
116 // on a work list for later generation and instead generate a jump. The
117 // destination of the jump is resolved later when the code is generated.
118 //
119 // Actual regular expression code generation.
120 //
121 // Code generation is actually more complicated than the above. In order to
122 // improve the efficiency of the generated code some optimizations are
123 // performed
124 //
125 // * Choice nodes have 1-character lookahead.
126 // A choice node looks at the following character and eliminates some of
127 // the choices immediately based on that character. This is not yet
128 // implemented.
129 // * Simple greedy loops store reduced backtracking information. We call
130 // these fixed length loops
131 // A quantifier like /.*foo/m will greedily match the whole input. It will
132 // then need to backtrack to a point where it can match "foo". The naive
133 // implementation of this would push each character position onto the
134 // backtracking stack, then pop them off one by one. This would use space
135 // proportional to the length of the input string. However since the "."
136 // can only match in one way and always has a constant length (in this case
137 // of 1) it suffices to store the current position on the top of the stack
138 // once. Matching now becomes merely incrementing the current position and
139 // backtracking becomes decrementing the current position and checking the
140 // result against the stored current position. This is faster and saves
141 // space.
142 // * The current state is virtualized.
143 // This is used to defer expensive operations until it is clear that they
144 // are needed and to generate code for a node more than once, allowing
145 // specialized an efficient versions of the code to be created. This is
146 // explained in the section below.
147 //
148 // Execution state virtualization.
149 //
150 // Instead of emitting code, nodes that manipulate the state can record their
151 // manipulation in an object called the Trace. The Trace object can record a
152 // current position offset, an optional backtrack code location on the top of
153 // the virtualized backtrack stack and some register changes. When a node is
154 // to be emitted it can flush the Trace or update it. Flushing the Trace
155 // will emit code to bring the actual state into line with the virtual state.
156 // Avoiding flushing the state can postpone some work (e.g. updates of capture
157 // registers). Postponing work can save time when executing the regular
158 // expression since it may be found that the work never has to be done as a
159 // failure to match can occur. In addition it is much faster to jump to a
160 // known backtrack code location than it is to pop an unknown backtrack
161 // location from the stack and jump there.
162 //
163 // The virtual state found in the Trace affects code generation. For example
164 // the virtual state contains the difference between the actual current
165 // position and the virtual current position, and matching code needs to use
166 // this offset to attempt a match in the correct location of the input
167 // string. Therefore code generated for a non-trivial trace is specialized
168 // to that trace. The code generator therefore has the ability to generate
169 // code for each node several times. In order to limit the size of the
170 // generated code there is an arbitrary limit on how many specialized sets of
171 // code may be generated for a given node. If the limit is reached, the
172 // trace is flushed and a generic version of the code for a node is emitted.
173 // This is subsequently used for that node. The code emitted for non-generic
174 // trace is not recorded in the node and so it cannot currently be reused in
175 // the event that code generation is requested for an identical trace.
176

263 RegExpCompiler::CompilationResult RegExpCompiler::Assemble(
264  Isolate* isolate, RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler, RegExpNode* start,
265  int capture_count, DirectHandle<String> pattern) {
266  macro_assembler_ = macro_assembler;
267 
268  ZoneVector<RegExpNode*> work_list(zone());
269  work_list_ = &work_list;
270  Label fail;
271  macro_assembler_->PushBacktrack(&fail);
272  Trace new_trace;
273  start->Emit(this, &new_trace);
274  macro_assembler_->BindJumpTarget(&fail);
275  macro_assembler_->Fail();
276  while (!work_list.empty()) {
277  RegExpNode* node = work_list.back();
278  work_list.pop_back();
279  node->set_on_work_list(false);
280  if (!node->label()->is_bound()) node->Emit(this, &new_trace);
281  }
282  if (reg_exp_too_big_) {
283  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
284  FATAL("Aborting on excess zone allocation");
285  }
286  macro_assembler_->AbortedCodeGeneration();
287  return CompilationResult::RegExpTooBig();
288  }
289 
290  DirectHandle<HeapObject> code = macro_assembler_->GetCode(pattern, flags_);
291  isolate->IncreaseTotalRegexpCodeGenerated(code);
292  work_list_ = nullptr;
293 
294  return {code, next_register_};
295 }

304 bool Trace::GetStoredPosition(int reg, int* cp_offset) const {
305  DCHECK_EQ(0, *cp_offset);
306  for (auto trace : *this) {
307  if (trace->has_action() && trace->action()->Mentions(reg)) {
308  if (trace->action_->action_type() == ActionNode::CLEAR_POSITION ||
309  trace->action_->action_type() == ActionNode::RESTORE_POSITION) {
310  *cp_offset = trace->next_->cp_offset();
311  return true;
312  } else {
313  return false;
314  }
315  }
316  }
317  return false;
318 }

320 // A (dynamically-sized) set of unsigned integers that behaves especially well
321 // on small integers (< kFirstLimit). May do zone-allocation.
322 class DynamicBitSet : public ZoneObject {
323  public:
324  V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool Get(unsigned value) const {
325  if (value < kFirstLimit) {
326  return (first_ & (1 << value)) != 0;
327  } else if (remaining_ == nullptr) {
328  return false;
329  } else {
330  return remaining_->Contains(value);
331  }
332  }
333 
334  // Destructively set a value in this set.
335  void Set(unsigned value, Zone* zone) {
336  if (value < kFirstLimit) {
337  first_ |= (1 << value);
338  } else {
339  if (remaining_ == nullptr)
340  remaining_ = zone->New<ZoneList<unsigned>>(1, zone);
341  if (remaining_->is_empty() || !remaining_->Contains(value))
342  remaining_->Add(value, zone);
343  }
344  }
345 
346  private:
347  static constexpr unsigned kFirstLimit = 32;
348 
349  uint32_t first_ = 0;
350  ZoneList<unsigned>* remaining_ = nullptr;
351 };
352 
353 int Trace::FindAffectedRegisters(DynamicBitSet* affected_registers,
354  Zone* zone) {
355  int max_register = RegExpCompiler::kNoRegister;
356  for (auto trace : *this) {
357  if (ActionNode* action = trace->action_) {
358  int to = action->register_to();
359  for (int i = action->register_from(); i <= to; i++) {
360  affected_registers->Set(i, zone);
361  }
362  if (to > max_register) max_register = to;
363  }
364  }
365  return max_register;
366 }
367 
368 void Trace::RestoreAffectedRegisters(RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler,
369  int max_register,
370  const DynamicBitSet& registers_to_pop,
371  const DynamicBitSet& registers_to_clear) {
372  for (int reg = max_register; reg >= 0; reg--) {
373  if (registers_to_pop.Get(reg)) {
374  assembler->PopRegister(reg);
375  } else if (registers_to_clear.Get(reg)) {
376  int clear_to = reg;
377  while (reg > 0 && registers_to_clear.Get(reg - 1)) {
378  reg--;
379  }
380  assembler->ClearRegisters(reg, clear_to);
381  }
382  }
383 }

385 void Trace::PerformDeferredActions(RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler,
386  int max_register,
387  const DynamicBitSet& affected_registers,
388  DynamicBitSet* registers_to_pop,
389  DynamicBitSet* registers_to_clear,
390  Zone* zone) {
391  // Count pushes performed to force a stack limit check occasionally.
392  int pushes = 0;
393 
394  for (int reg = 0; reg <= max_register; reg++) {
395  if (!affected_registers.Get(reg)) continue;
396 
397  // The chronologically first deferred action in the trace
398  // is used to infer the action needed to restore a register
399  // to its previous state (or not, if it's safe to ignore it).
400  enum DeferredActionUndoType { IGNORE, RESTORE, CLEAR };
401  DeferredActionUndoType undo_action = IGNORE;
402 
403  int value = 0;
404  bool absolute = false;
405  bool clear = false;
406  static const int kNoStore = kMinInt;
407  int store_position = kNoStore;
408  // This is a little tricky because we are scanning the actions in reverse
409  // historical order (newest first).
410  for (auto trace : *this) {
411  ActionNode* action = trace->action_;
412  if (!action) continue;
413  if (action->Mentions(reg)) {
414  switch (action->action_type()) {
415  case ActionNode::SET_REGISTER_FOR_LOOP: {
416  if (!absolute) {
417  value += action->value();
418  absolute = true;
419  }
420  // SET_REGISTER_FOR_LOOP is only used for newly introduced loop
421  // counters. They can have a significant previous value if they
422  // occur in a loop. TODO(lrn): Propagate this information, so
423  // we can set undo_action to IGNORE if we know there is no value to
424  // restore.
425  undo_action = RESTORE;
426  DCHECK_EQ(store_position, kNoStore);
427  DCHECK(!clear);
428  break;
429  }
430  case ActionNode::INCREMENT_REGISTER:
431  if (!absolute) {
432  value++;
433  }
434  DCHECK_EQ(store_position, kNoStore);
435  DCHECK(!clear);
436  undo_action = RESTORE;
437  break;
438  case ActionNode::CLEAR_POSITION:
439  case ActionNode::RESTORE_POSITION: {
440  if (!clear && store_position == kNoStore) {
441  store_position = trace->next()->cp_offset();
442  }
443 
444  // For captures we know that stores and clears alternate.
445  // Other register, are never cleared, and if the occur
446  // inside a loop, they might be assigned more than once.
447  if (reg <= 1) {
448  // Registers zero and one, aka "capture zero", is
449  // always set correctly if we succeed. There is no
450  // need to undo a setting on backtrack, because we
451  // will set it again or fail.
452  undo_action = IGNORE;
453  } else {
454  if (action->action_type() == ActionNode::CLEAR_POSITION) {
455  undo_action = CLEAR;
456  } else {
457  undo_action = RESTORE;
458  }
459  }
460  DCHECK(!absolute);
461  DCHECK_EQ(value, 0);
462  break;
463  }
464  case ActionNode::CLEAR_CAPTURES: {
465  // Since we're scanning in reverse order, if we've already
466  // set the position we have to ignore historically earlier
467  // clearing operations.
468  if (store_position == kNoStore) {
469  clear = true;
470  }
471  undo_action = RESTORE;
472  DCHECK(!absolute);
473  DCHECK_EQ(value, 0);
474  break;
475  }
476  default:
477  UNREACHABLE();
478  }
479  }
480  }
481  // Prepare for the undo-action (e.g., push if it's going to be popped).
482  if (undo_action == RESTORE) {
483  pushes++;
484  RegExpMacroAssembler::StackCheckFlag stack_check =
485  RegExpMacroAssembler::kNoStackLimitCheck;
486  DCHECK_GT(assembler->stack_limit_slack_slot_count(), 0);
487  if (pushes == assembler->stack_limit_slack_slot_count()) {
488  stack_check = RegExpMacroAssembler::kCheckStackLimit;
489  pushes = 0;
490  }
491 
492  assembler->PushRegister(reg, stack_check);
493  registers_to_pop->Set(reg, zone);
494  } else if (undo_action == CLEAR) {
495  registers_to_clear->Set(reg, zone);
496  }
497  // Perform the chronologically last action (or accumulated increment)
498  // for the register.
499  if (store_position != kNoStore) {
500  assembler->WriteCurrentPositionToRegister(reg, store_position);
501  } else if (clear) {
502  assembler->ClearRegisters(reg, reg);
503  } else if (absolute) {
504  assembler->SetRegister(reg, value);
505  } else if (value != 0) {
506  assembler->AdvanceRegister(reg, value);
507  }
508  }
509 }
510 
511 // This is called as we come into a loop choice node and some other tricky
512 // nodes. It normalizes the state of the code generator to ensure we can
513 // generate generic code. If the mode indicates that we are in a success
514 // situation then don't push anything, because the stack is about to be
515 // discarded, and also don't update the current position.
516 void Trace::Flush(RegExpCompiler* compiler, RegExpNode* successor,
517  Trace::FlushMode mode) {
518  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
519 
520  DCHECK(!is_trivial());
521 
522  // Normally we don't need to update the current position register if we are
523  // about to stop because we had a successful match, but the global mode
524  // requires the current position register to be updated so it can start the
525  // next match. TODO(erikcorry): Perhaps it should use capture register 1
526  // instead.
527  bool update_current_position =
528  cp_offset_ != 0 && (mode != kFlushSuccess || assembler->global());
529 
530  if (!has_any_actions() && (backtrack() == nullptr || mode == kFlushSuccess)) {
531  // Here we just have some deferred cp advances to fix and we are back to
532  // a normal situation. We may also have to forget some information gained
533  // through a quick check that was already performed.
534  if (update_current_position) assembler->AdvanceCurrentPosition(cp_offset_);
535  // Create a new trivial state and generate the node with that.
536  Trace new_state;
537  successor->Emit(compiler, &new_state);
538  return;
539  }
540 
541  // Generate deferred actions here along with code to undo them again.
542  DynamicBitSet affected_registers;
543 
544  if (backtrack() != nullptr && mode != kFlushSuccess) {
545  // Here we have a concrete backtrack location. These are set up by choice
546  // nodes and so they indicate that we have a deferred save of the current
547  // position which we may need to emit here.
548  assembler->PushCurrentPosition();
549  }
550 
551  int max_register =
552  FindAffectedRegisters(&affected_registers, compiler->zone());
553  DynamicBitSet registers_to_pop;
554  DynamicBitSet registers_to_clear;
555  PerformDeferredActions(assembler, max_register, affected_registers,
556  &registers_to_pop, &registers_to_clear,
557  compiler->zone());
558  if (update_current_position) assembler->AdvanceCurrentPosition(cp_offset_);
559 
560  if (mode == kFlushSuccess) {
561  Trace new_state;
562  successor->Emit(compiler, &new_state);
563  return;
564  }
565 
566  // Create a new trivial state and generate the node with that.
567  Label undo;
568  assembler->PushBacktrack(&undo);
569  if (successor->KeepRecursing(compiler)) {
570  Trace new_state;
571  successor->Emit(compiler, &new_state);
572  } else {
573  compiler->AddWork(successor);
574  assembler->GoTo(successor->label());
575  }
576 
577  // On backtrack we need to restore state.
578  assembler->BindJumpTarget(&undo);
579  RestoreAffectedRegisters(assembler, max_register, registers_to_pop,
580  registers_to_clear);
581  if (backtrack() == nullptr) {
582  assembler->Backtrack();
583  } else {
584  assembler->PopCurrentPosition();
585  assembler->GoTo(backtrack());
586  }
587 }

589 void NegativeSubmatchSuccess::Emit(RegExpCompiler* compiler, Trace* trace) {
590  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
591 
592  // Omit flushing the trace. We discard the entire stack frame anyway.
593 
594  if (!label()->is_bound()) {
595  // We are completely independent of the trace, since we ignore it,
596  // so this code can be used as the generic version.
597  assembler->Bind(label());
598  }
599 
600  // Throw away everything on the backtrack stack since the start
601  // of the negative submatch and restore the character position.
602  assembler->ReadCurrentPositionFromRegister(current_position_register_);
603  assembler->ReadStackPointerFromRegister(stack_pointer_register_);
604  if (clear_capture_count_ > 0) {
605  // Clear any captures that might have been performed during the success
606  // of the body of the negative look-ahead.
607  int clear_capture_end = clear_capture_start_ + clear_capture_count_ - 1;
608  assembler->ClearRegisters(clear_capture_start_, clear_capture_end);
609  }
610  // Now that we have unwound the stack we find at the top of the stack the
611  // backtrack that the BeginNegativeSubmatch node got.
612  assembler->Backtrack();
613 }
614 
615 void EndNode::Emit(RegExpCompiler* compiler, Trace* trace) {
616  if (!trace->is_trivial()) {
617  DCHECK(action_ == ACCEPT);
618  trace->Flush(compiler, this, Trace::kFlushSuccess);
619  return;
620  }
621  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
622  if (!label()->is_bound()) {
623  assembler->Bind(label());
624  }
625  switch (action_) {
626  case ACCEPT:
627  assembler->Succeed();
628  return;
629  case BACKTRACK:
630  assembler->GoTo(trace->backtrack());
631  return;
632  case NEGATIVE_SUBMATCH_SUCCESS:
633  // This case is handled in a different virtual method.
634  UNREACHABLE();
635  }
636  UNIMPLEMENTED();
637 }

728 void ChoiceNode::GenerateGuard(RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler,
729  Guard* guard, Trace* trace) {
730  switch (guard->op()) {
731  case Guard::LT:
732  DCHECK(!trace->mentions_reg(guard->reg()));
733  macro_assembler->IfRegisterGE(guard->reg(), guard->value(),
734  trace->backtrack());
735  break;
736  case Guard::GEQ:
737  DCHECK(!trace->mentions_reg(guard->reg()));
738  macro_assembler->IfRegisterLT(guard->reg(), guard->value(),
739  trace->backtrack());
740  break;
741  }
742 }

746 #ifdef DEBUG
747 bool ContainsOnlyUtf16CodeUnits(unibrow::uchar* chars, int length) {
748  static_assert(sizeof(unibrow::uchar) == 4);
749  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
750  if (chars[i] > String::kMaxUtf16CodeUnit) return false;
751  }
752  return true;
753 }

756 // Returns the number of characters in the equivalence class, omitting those
757 // that cannot occur in the source string because it is Latin1. This is called
758 // both for unicode modes /ui and /vi, and also for legacy case independent
759 // mode /i. In the case of Unicode modes we handled surrogate pair expansions
760 // earlier so at this point it's all about single-code-unit expansions.
761 int GetCaseIndependentLetters(Isolate* isolate, base::uc16 character,
762  RegExpCompiler* compiler, unibrow::uchar* letters,
763  int letter_length) {
764  bool one_byte_subject = compiler->one_byte();
765  bool unicode = IsEitherUnicode(compiler->flags());
766  static const base::uc16 kMaxAscii = 0x7f;
767  if (!unicode && character <= kMaxAscii) {
768  // Fast case for common characters.
769  base::uc16 upper = character & ~0x20;
770  if ('A' <= upper && upper <= 'Z') {
771  letters[0] = upper;
772  letters[1] = upper | 0x20;
773  return 2;
774  }
775  letters[0] = character;
776  return 1;
777  }
778 #ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
779 
780  if (!unicode && RegExpCaseFolding::IgnoreSet().contains(character)) {
781  if (one_byte_subject && character > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) {
782  // This function promises not to return a character that is impossible
783  // for the subject encoding.
784  return 0;
785  }
786  letters[0] = character;
787  DCHECK(ContainsOnlyUtf16CodeUnits(letters, 1));
788  return 1;
789  }
790  bool in_special_add_set =
791  RegExpCaseFolding::SpecialAddSet().contains(character);
792 
793  icu::UnicodeSet set;
794  set.add(character);
795  set = set.closeOver(unicode ? USET_SIMPLE_CASE_INSENSITIVE
796  : USET_CASE_INSENSITIVE);
797 
798  UChar32 canon = 0;
799  if (in_special_add_set && !unicode) {
800  canon = RegExpCaseFolding::Canonicalize(character);
801  }
802 
803  int32_t range_count = set.getRangeCount();
804  int items = 0;
805  for (int32_t i = 0; i < range_count; i++) {
806  UChar32 start = set.getRangeStart(i);
807  UChar32 end = set.getRangeEnd(i);
808  CHECK(end - start + items <= letter_length);
809  for (UChar32 cu = start; cu <= end; cu++) {
810  if (one_byte_subject && cu > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) continue;
811  if (!unicode && in_special_add_set &&
812  RegExpCaseFolding::Canonicalize(cu) != canon) {
813  continue;
814  }
815  letters[items++] = static_cast<unibrow::uchar>(cu);
816  }
817  }
818  DCHECK(ContainsOnlyUtf16CodeUnits(letters, items));
819  return items;
820 #else
821  int length =
822  isolate->jsregexp_uncanonicalize()->get(character, '\0', letters);
823  // Unibrow returns 0 or 1 for characters where case independence is
824  // trivial.
825  if (length == 0) {
826  letters[0] = character;
827  length = 1;
828  }
829 
830  if (one_byte_subject) {
831  int new_length = 0;
832  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
833  if (letters[i] <= String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) {
834  letters[new_length++] = letters[i];
835  }
836  }
837  length = new_length;
838  }
839 
840  DCHECK(ContainsOnlyUtf16CodeUnits(letters, length));
841  return length;
842 #endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
843 }

845 inline bool EmitSimpleCharacter(Isolate* isolate, RegExpCompiler* compiler,
846  base::uc16 c, Label* on_failure, int cp_offset,
847  bool check, bool preloaded) {
848  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
849  bool bound_checked = false;
850  if (!preloaded) {
851  assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(cp_offset, on_failure, check);
852  bound_checked = true;
853  }
854  assembler->CheckNotCharacter(c, on_failure);
855  return bound_checked;
856 }

858 // Only emits non-letters (things that don't have case). Only used for case
859 // independent matches.
860 inline bool EmitAtomNonLetter(Isolate* isolate, RegExpCompiler* compiler,
861  base::uc16 c, Label* on_failure, int cp_offset,
862  bool check, bool preloaded) {
863  RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
864  bool one_byte = compiler->one_byte();
865  unibrow::uchar chars[4];
866  int length = GetCaseIndependentLetters(isolate, c, compiler, chars, 4);
867  if (length < 1) {
868  // This can't match. Must be an one-byte subject and a non-one-byte
869  // character. We do not need to do anything since the one-byte pass
870  // already handled this.
871  CHECK(one_byte);
872  return false; // Bounds not checked.
873  }
874  bool checked = false;
875  // We handle the length > 1 case in a later pass.
876  if (length == 1) {
877  // GetCaseIndependentLetters promises not to return characters that can't
878  // match because of the subject encoding. This case is already handled by
879  // the one-byte pass.
880  CHECK_IMPLIES(one_byte, chars[0] <= String::kMaxOneByteCharCodeU);
881  if (!preloaded) {
882  macro_assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(cp_offset, on_failure, check);
883  checked = check;
884  }
885  macro_assembler->CheckNotCharacter(chars[0], on_failure);
886  }
887  return checked;
888 }

890 bool ShortCutEmitCharacterPair(RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler,
891  bool one_byte, base::uc16 c1, base::uc16 c2,
892  Label* on_failure) {
893  const uint32_t char_mask = CharMask(one_byte);
894  base::uc16 exor = c1 ^ c2;
895  // Check whether exor has only one bit set.
896  if (((exor - 1) & exor) == 0) {
897  // If c1 and c2 differ only by one bit.
898  // Ecma262UnCanonicalize always gives the highest number last.
899  DCHECK(c2 > c1);
900  base::uc16 mask = char_mask ^ exor;
901  macro_assembler->CheckNotCharacterAfterAnd(c1, mask, on_failure);
902  return true;
903  }
904  DCHECK(c2 > c1);
905  base::uc16 diff = c2 - c1;
906  if (((diff - 1) & diff) == 0 && c1 >= diff) {
907  // If the characters differ by 2^n but don't differ by one bit then
908  // subtract the difference from the found character, then do the or
909  // trick. We avoid the theoretical case where negative numbers are
910  // involved in order to simplify code generation.
911  base::uc16 mask = char_mask ^ diff;
912  macro_assembler->CheckNotCharacterAfterMinusAnd(c1 - diff, diff, mask,
913  on_failure);
914  return true;
915  }
916  return false;
917 }
918 
919 // Only emits letters (things that have case). Only used for case independent
920 // matches.
921 inline bool EmitAtomLetter(Isolate* isolate, RegExpCompiler* compiler,
922  base::uc16 c, Label* on_failure, int cp_offset,
923  bool check, bool preloaded) {
924  RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
925  bool one_byte = compiler->one_byte();
926  unibrow::uchar chars[4];
927  int length = GetCaseIndependentLetters(isolate, c, compiler, chars, 4);
928  // The 0 and 1 case are handled by earlier passes.
929  if (length <= 1) return false;
930  // We may not need to check against the end of the input string
931  // if this character lies before a character that matched.
932  if (!preloaded) {
933  macro_assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(cp_offset, on_failure, check);
934  }
935  Label ok;
936  switch (length) {
937  case 2: {
938  if (ShortCutEmitCharacterPair(macro_assembler, one_byte, chars[0],
939  chars[1], on_failure)) {
940  } else {
941  macro_assembler->CheckCharacter(chars[0], &ok);
942  macro_assembler->CheckNotCharacter(chars[1], on_failure);
943  macro_assembler->Bind(&ok);
944  }
945  break;
946  }
947  case 4:
948  macro_assembler->CheckCharacter(chars[3], &ok);
949  [[fallthrough]];
950  case 3:
951  macro_assembler->CheckCharacter(chars[0], &ok);
952  macro_assembler->CheckCharacter(chars[1], &ok);
953  macro_assembler->CheckNotCharacter(chars[2], on_failure);
954  macro_assembler->Bind(&ok);
955  break;
956  default:
957  UNREACHABLE();
958  }
959  return true;
960 }

962 void EmitBoundaryTest(RegExpMacroAssembler* masm, int border,
963  Label* fall_through, Label* above_or_equal,
964  Label* below) {
965  if (below != fall_through) {
966  masm->CheckCharacterLT(border, below);
967  if (above_or_equal != fall_through) masm->GoTo(above_or_equal);
968  } else {
969  masm->CheckCharacterGT(border - 1, above_or_equal);
970  }
971 }

973 void EmitDoubleBoundaryTest(RegExpMacroAssembler* masm, int first, int last,
974  Label* fall_through, Label* in_range,
975  Label* out_of_range) {
976  if (in_range == fall_through) {
977  if (first == last) {
978  masm->CheckNotCharacter(first, out_of_range);
979  } else {
980  masm->CheckCharacterNotInRange(first, last, out_of_range);
981  }
982  } else {
983  if (first == last) {
984  masm->CheckCharacter(first, in_range);
985  } else {
986  masm->CheckCharacterInRange(first, last, in_range);
987  }
988  if (out_of_range != fall_through) masm->GoTo(out_of_range);
989  }
990 }

992 // even_label is for ranges[i] to ranges[i + 1] where i - start_index is even.
993 // odd_label is for ranges[i] to ranges[i + 1] where i - start_index is odd.
994 void EmitUseLookupTable(RegExpMacroAssembler* masm,
995  ZoneList<base::uc32>* ranges, uint32_t start_index,
996  uint32_t end_index, base::uc32 min_char,
997  Label* fall_through, Label* even_label,
998  Label* odd_label) {
999  static const uint32_t kSize = RegExpMacroAssembler::kTableSize;
1000  static const uint32_t kMask = RegExpMacroAssembler::kTableMask;
1001 
1002  base::uc32 base = (min_char & ~kMask);
1003  USE(base);
1004 
1005  // Assert that everything is on one kTableSize page.
1006  for (uint32_t i = start_index; i <= end_index; i++) {
1007  DCHECK_EQ(ranges->at(i) & ~kMask, base);
1008  }
1009  DCHECK(start_index == 0 || (ranges->at(start_index - 1) & ~kMask) <= base);
1010 
1011  char templ[kSize];
1012  Label* on_bit_set;
1013  Label* on_bit_clear;
1014  int bit;
1015  if (even_label == fall_through) {
1016  on_bit_set = odd_label;
1017  on_bit_clear = even_label;
1018  bit = 1;
1019  } else {
1020  on_bit_set = even_label;
1021  on_bit_clear = odd_label;
1022  bit = 0;
1023  }
1024  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < (ranges->at(start_index) & kMask) && i < kSize;
1025  i++) {
1026  templ[i] = bit;
1027  }
1028  uint32_t j = 0;
1029  bit ^= 1;
1030  for (uint32_t i = start_index; i < end_index; i++) {
1031  for (j = (ranges->at(i) & kMask); j < (ranges->at(i + 1) & kMask); j++) {
1032  templ[j] = bit;
1033  }
1034  bit ^= 1;
1035  }
1036  for (uint32_t i = j; i < kSize; i++) {
1037  templ[i] = bit;
1038  }
1039  Factory* factory = masm->isolate()->factory();
1040  // TODO(erikcorry): Cache these.
1041  Handle<ByteArray> ba = factory->NewByteArray(kSize, AllocationType::kOld);
1042  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < kSize; i++) {
1043  ba->set(i, templ[i]);
1044  }
1045  masm->CheckBitInTable(ba, on_bit_set);
1046  if (on_bit_clear != fall_through) masm->GoTo(on_bit_clear);
1047 }

1049 void CutOutRange(RegExpMacroAssembler* masm, ZoneList<base::uc32>* ranges,
1050  uint32_t start_index, uint32_t end_index, uint32_t cut_index,
1051  Label* even_label, Label* odd_label) {
1052  bool odd = (((cut_index - start_index) & 1) == 1);
1053  Label* in_range_label = odd ? odd_label : even_label;
1054  Label dummy;
1055  EmitDoubleBoundaryTest(masm, ranges->at(cut_index),
1056  ranges->at(cut_index + 1) - 1, &dummy, in_range_label,
1057  &dummy);
1058  DCHECK(!dummy.is_linked());
1059  // Cut out the single range by rewriting the array. This creates a new
1060  // range that is a merger of the two ranges on either side of the one we
1061  // are cutting out. The oddity of the labels is preserved.
1062  for (uint32_t j = cut_index; j > start_index; j--) {
1063  ranges->at(j) = ranges->at(j - 1);
1064  }
1065  for (uint32_t j = cut_index + 1; j < end_index; j++) {
1066  ranges->at(j) = ranges->at(j + 1);
1067  }
1068 }

1070 // Unicode case. Split the search space into kSize spaces that are handled
1071 // with recursion.
1072 void SplitSearchSpace(ZoneList<base::uc32>* ranges, uint32_t start_index,
1073  uint32_t end_index, uint32_t* new_start_index,
1074  uint32_t* new_end_index, base::uc32* border) {
1075  static const uint32_t kSize = RegExpMacroAssembler::kTableSize;
1076  static const uint32_t kMask = RegExpMacroAssembler::kTableMask;
1077 
1078  base::uc32 first = ranges->at(start_index);
1079  base::uc32 last = ranges->at(end_index) - 1;
1080 
1081  *new_start_index = start_index;
1082  *border = (ranges->at(start_index) & ~kMask) + kSize;
1083  while (*new_start_index < end_index) {
1084  if (ranges->at(*new_start_index) > *border) break;
1085  (*new_start_index)++;
1086  }
1087  // new_start_index is the index of the first edge that is beyond the
1088  // current kSize space.
1089 
1090  // For very large search spaces we do a binary chop search of the non-Latin1
1091  // space instead of just going to the end of the current kSize space. The
1092  // heuristics are complicated a little by the fact that any 128-character
1093  // encoding space can be quickly tested with a table lookup, so we don't
1094  // wish to do binary chop search at a smaller granularity than that. A
1095  // 128-character space can take up a lot of space in the ranges array if,
1096  // for example, we only want to match every second character (eg. the lower
1097  // case characters on some Unicode pages).
1098  uint32_t binary_chop_index = (end_index + start_index) / 2;
1099  // The first test ensures that we get to the code that handles the Latin1
1100  // range with a single not-taken branch, speeding up this important
1101  // character range (even non-Latin1 charset-based text has spaces and
1102  // punctuation).
1103  if (*border - 1 > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode && // Latin1 case.
1104  end_index - start_index > (*new_start_index - start_index) * 2 &&
1105  last - first > kSize * 2 && binary_chop_index > *new_start_index &&
1106  ranges->at(binary_chop_index) >= first + 2 * kSize) {
1107  uint32_t scan_forward_for_section_border = binary_chop_index;
1108  uint32_t new_border = (ranges->at(binary_chop_index) | kMask) + 1;
1109 
1110  while (scan_forward_for_section_border < end_index) {
1111  if (ranges->at(scan_forward_for_section_border) > new_border) {
1112  *new_start_index = scan_forward_for_section_border;
1113  *border = new_border;
1114  break;
1115  }
1116  scan_forward_for_section_border++;
1117  }
1118  }
1119 
1120  DCHECK(*new_start_index > start_index);
1121  *new_end_index = *new_start_index - 1;
1122  if (ranges->at(*new_end_index) == *border) {
1123  (*new_end_index)--;
1124  }
1125  if (*border >= ranges->at(end_index)) {
1126  *border = ranges->at(end_index);
1127  *new_start_index = end_index; // Won't be used.
1128  *new_end_index = end_index - 1;
1129  }
1130 }
1131 
1132 // Gets a series of segment boundaries representing a character class. If the
1133 // character is in the range between an even and an odd boundary (counting from
1134 // start_index) then go to even_label, otherwise go to odd_label. We already
1135 // know that the character is in the range of min_char to max_char inclusive.
1136 // Either label can be nullptr indicating backtracking. Either label can also
1137 // be equal to the fall_through label.
1138 void GenerateBranches(RegExpMacroAssembler* masm, ZoneList<base::uc32>* ranges,
1139  uint32_t start_index, uint32_t end_index,
1140  base::uc32 min_char, base::uc32 max_char,
1141  Label* fall_through, Label* even_label,
1142  Label* odd_label) {
1143  DCHECK_LE(min_char, String::kMaxUtf16CodeUnit);
1144  DCHECK_LE(max_char, String::kMaxUtf16CodeUnit);
1145 
1146  base::uc32 first = ranges->at(start_index);
1147  base::uc32 last = ranges->at(end_index) - 1;
1148 
1149  DCHECK_LT(min_char, first);
1150 
1151  // Just need to test if the character is before or on-or-after
1152  // a particular character.
1153  if (start_index == end_index) {
1154  EmitBoundaryTest(masm, first, fall_through, even_label, odd_label);
1155  return;
1156  }
1157 
1158  // Another almost trivial case: There is one interval in the middle that is
1159  // different from the end intervals.
1160  if (start_index + 1 == end_index) {
1161  EmitDoubleBoundaryTest(masm, first, last, fall_through, even_label,
1162  odd_label);
1163  return;
1164  }
1165 
1166  // It's not worth using table lookup if there are very few intervals in the
1167  // character class.
1168  if (end_index - start_index <= 6) {
1169  // It is faster to test for individual characters, so we look for those
1170  // first, then try arbitrary ranges in the second round.
1171  static uint32_t kNoCutIndex = -1;
1172  uint32_t cut = kNoCutIndex;
1173  for (uint32_t i = start_index; i < end_index; i++) {
1174  if (ranges->at(i) == ranges->at(i + 1) - 1) {
1175  cut = i;
1176  break;
1177  }
1178  }
1179  if (cut == kNoCutIndex) cut = start_index;
1180  CutOutRange(masm, ranges, start_index, end_index, cut, even_label,
1181  odd_label);
1182  DCHECK_GE(end_index - start_index, 2);
1183  GenerateBranches(masm, ranges, start_index + 1, end_index - 1, min_char,
1184  max_char, fall_through, even_label, odd_label);
1185  return;
1186  }
1187 
1188  // If there are a lot of intervals in the regexp, then we will use tables to
1189  // determine whether the character is inside or outside the character class.
1190  static const int kBits = RegExpMacroAssembler::kTableSizeBits;
1191 
1192  if ((max_char >> kBits) == (min_char >> kBits)) {
1193  EmitUseLookupTable(masm, ranges, start_index, end_index, min_char,
1194  fall_through, even_label, odd_label);
1195  return;
1196  }
1197 
1198  if ((min_char >> kBits) != first >> kBits) {
1199  masm->CheckCharacterLT(first, odd_label);
1200  GenerateBranches(masm, ranges, start_index + 1, end_index, first, max_char,
1201  fall_through, odd_label, even_label);
1202  return;
1203  }
1204 
1205  uint32_t new_start_index = 0;
1206  uint32_t new_end_index = 0;
1207  base::uc32 border = 0;
1208 
1209  SplitSearchSpace(ranges, start_index, end_index, &new_start_index,
1210  &new_end_index, &border);
1211 
1212  Label handle_rest;
1213  Label* above = &handle_rest;
1214  if (border == last + 1) {
1215  // We didn't find any section that started after the limit, so everything
1216  // above the border is one of the terminal labels.
1217  above = (end_index & 1) != (start_index & 1) ? odd_label : even_label;
1218  DCHECK(new_end_index == end_index - 1);
1219  }
1220 
1221  DCHECK_LE(start_index, new_end_index);
1222  DCHECK_LE(new_start_index, end_index);
1223  DCHECK_LT(start_index, new_start_index);
1224  DCHECK_LT(new_end_index, end_index);
1225  DCHECK(new_end_index + 1 == new_start_index ||
1226  (new_end_index + 2 == new_start_index &&
1227  border == ranges->at(new_end_index + 1)));
1228  DCHECK_LT(min_char, border - 1);
1229  DCHECK_LT(border, max_char);
1230  DCHECK_LT(ranges->at(new_end_index), border);
1231  DCHECK(border < ranges->at(new_start_index) ||
1232  (border == ranges->at(new_start_index) &&
1233  new_start_index == end_index && new_end_index == end_index - 1 &&
1234  border == last + 1));
1235  DCHECK(new_start_index == 0 || border >= ranges->at(new_start_index - 1));
1236 
1237  masm->CheckCharacterGT(border - 1, above);
1238  Label dummy;
1239  GenerateBranches(masm, ranges, start_index, new_end_index, min_char,
1240  border - 1, &dummy, even_label, odd_label);
1241  if (handle_rest.is_linked()) {
1242  masm->Bind(&handle_rest);
1243  bool flip = (new_start_index & 1) != (start_index & 1);
1244  GenerateBranches(masm, ranges, new_start_index, end_index, border, max_char,
1245  &dummy, flip ? odd_label : even_label,
1246  flip ? even_label : odd_label);
1247  }
1248 }

1250 void EmitClassRanges(RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler,
1251  RegExpClassRanges* cr, bool one_byte, Label* on_failure,
1252  int cp_offset, bool check_offset, bool preloaded,
1253  Zone* zone) {
1254  ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges = cr->ranges(zone);
1255  CharacterRange::Canonicalize(ranges);
1256 
1257  // Now that all processing (like case-insensitivity) is done, clamp the
1258  // ranges to the set of ranges that may actually occur in the subject string.
1259  if (one_byte) CharacterRange::ClampToOneByte(ranges);
1260 
1261  const int ranges_length = ranges->length();
1262  if (ranges_length == 0) {
1263  if (!cr->is_negated()) {
1264  macro_assembler->GoTo(on_failure);
1265  }
1266  if (check_offset) {
1267  macro_assembler->CheckPosition(cp_offset, on_failure);
1268  }
1269  return;
1270  }
1271 
1272  const base::uc32 max_char = MaxCodeUnit(one_byte);
1273  if (ranges_length == 1 && ranges->at(0).IsEverything(max_char)) {
1274  if (cr->is_negated()) {
1275  macro_assembler->GoTo(on_failure);
1276  } else {
1277  // This is a common case hit by non-anchored expressions.
1278  if (check_offset) {
1279  macro_assembler->CheckPosition(cp_offset, on_failure);
1280  }
1281  }
1282  return;
1283  }
1284 
1285  if (!preloaded) {
1286  macro_assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(cp_offset, on_failure, check_offset);
1287  }
1288 
1289  if (cr->is_standard(zone) && macro_assembler->CheckSpecialClassRanges(
1290  cr->standard_type(), on_failure)) {
1291  return;
1292  }
1293 
1294  static constexpr int kMaxRangesForInlineBranchGeneration = 16;
1295  if (ranges_length > kMaxRangesForInlineBranchGeneration) {
1296  // For large range sets, emit a more compact instruction sequence to avoid
1297  // a potentially problematic increase in code size.
1298  // Note the flipped logic below (we check InRange if negated, NotInRange if
1299  // not negated); this is necessary since the method falls through on
1300  // failure whereas we want to fall through on success.
1301  if (cr->is_negated()) {
1302  if (macro_assembler->CheckCharacterInRangeArray(ranges, on_failure)) {
1303  return;
1304  }
1305  } else {
1306  if (macro_assembler->CheckCharacterNotInRangeArray(ranges, on_failure)) {
1307  return;
1308  }
1309  }
1310  }
1311 
1312  // Generate a flat list of range boundaries for consumption by
1313  // GenerateBranches. See the comment on that function for how the list should
1314  // be structured
1315  ZoneList<base::uc32>* range_boundaries =
1316  zone->New<ZoneList<base::uc32>>(ranges_length * 2, zone);
1317 
1318  bool zeroth_entry_is_failure = !cr->is_negated();
1319 
1320  for (int i = 0; i < ranges_length; i++) {
1321  CharacterRange& range = ranges->at(i);
1322  if (range.from() == 0) {
1323  DCHECK_EQ(i, 0);
1324  zeroth_entry_is_failure = !zeroth_entry_is_failure;
1325  } else {
1326  range_boundaries->Add(range.from(), zone);
1327  }
1328  // `+ 1` to convert from inclusive to exclusive `to`.
1329  // [from, to] == [from, to+1[.
1330  range_boundaries->Add(range.to() + 1, zone);
1331  }
1332  int end_index = range_boundaries->length() - 1;
1333  if (range_boundaries->at(end_index) > max_char) {
1334  end_index--;
1335  }
1336 
1337  Label fall_through;
1338  GenerateBranches(macro_assembler, range_boundaries,
1339  0, // start_index.
1340  end_index,
1341  0, // min_char.
1342  max_char, &fall_through,
1343  zeroth_entry_is_failure ? &fall_through : on_failure,
1344  zeroth_entry_is_failure ? on_failure : &fall_through);
1345  macro_assembler->Bind(&fall_through);
1346 }

1352 RegExpNode::LimitResult RegExpNode::LimitVersions(RegExpCompiler* compiler,
1353  Trace* trace) {
1354  // If we are generating a fixed length loop then don't stop and don't reuse
1355  // code.
1356  if (trace->fixed_length_loop_state() != nullptr) {
1357  return CONTINUE;
1358  }
1359 
1360  RegExpMacroAssembler* macro_assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
1361  if (trace->is_trivial()) {
1362  if (label_.is_bound() || on_work_list() || !KeepRecursing(compiler)) {
1363  // If a generic version is already scheduled to be generated or we have
1364  // recursed too deeply then just generate a jump to that code.
1365  macro_assembler->GoTo(&label_);
1366  // This will queue it up for generation of a generic version if it hasn't
1367  // already been queued.
1368  compiler->AddWork(this);
1369  return DONE;
1370  }
1371  // Generate generic version of the node and bind the label for later use.
1372  macro_assembler->Bind(&label_);
1373  return CONTINUE;
1374  }
1375 
1376  // We are being asked to make a non-generic version. Keep track of how many
1377  // non-generic versions we generate so as not to overdo it.
1378  trace_count_++;
1379  if (KeepRecursing(compiler) && compiler->optimize() &&
1380  trace_count_ < kMaxCopiesCodeGenerated) {
1381  return CONTINUE;
1382  }
1383 
1384  // If we get here code has been generated for this node too many times or
1385  // recursion is too deep. Time to switch to a generic version. The code for
1386  // generic versions above can handle deep recursion properly.
1387  bool was_limiting = compiler->limiting_recursion();
1388  compiler->set_limiting_recursion(true);
1389  trace->Flush(compiler, this);
1390  compiler->set_limiting_recursion(was_limiting);
1391  return DONE;
1392 }
1393 
1394 bool RegExpNode::KeepRecursing(RegExpCompiler* compiler) {
1395  return !compiler->limiting_recursion() &&
1396  compiler->recursion_depth() <= RegExpCompiler::kMaxRecursion;
1397 }

1399 void ActionNode::FillInBMInfo(Isolate* isolate, int offset, int budget,
1400  BoyerMooreLookahead* bm, bool not_at_start) {
1401  std::optional<RegExpFlags> old_flags;
1402  if (action_type_ == MODIFY_FLAGS) {
1403  // It is not guaranteed that we hit the resetting modify flags node, due to
1404  // recursion budget limitation for filling in BMInfo. Therefore we reset the
1405  // flags manually to the previous state after recursing.
1406  old_flags = bm->compiler()->flags();
1407  bm->compiler()->set_flags(flags());
1408  }
1409  if (action_type_ == BEGIN_POSITIVE_SUBMATCH) {
1410  // We use the node after the lookaround to fill in the eats_at_least info
1411  // so we have to use the same node to fill in the Boyer-Moore info.
1412  success_node()->on_success()->FillInBMInfo(isolate, offset, budget - 1, bm,
1413  not_at_start);
1414  } else if (action_type_ != POSITIVE_SUBMATCH_SUCCESS) {
1415  // We don't use the node after a positive submatch success because it
1416  // rewinds the position. Since we returned 0 as the eats_at_least value for
1417  // this node, we don't need to fill in any data.
1418  on_success()->FillInBMInfo(isolate, offset, budget - 1, bm, not_at_start);
1419  }
1420  SaveBMInfo(bm, not_at_start, offset);
1421  if (old_flags.has_value()) {
1422  bm->compiler()->set_flags(*old_flags);
1423  }
1424 }

1474 // Takes the left-most 1-bit and smears it out, setting all bits to its right.
1475 inline uint32_t SmearBitsRight(uint32_t v) {
1476  v |= v >> 1;
1477  v |= v >> 2;
1478  v |= v >> 4;
1479  v |= v >> 8;
1480  v |= v >> 16;
1481  return v;
1482 }

1486 bool QuickCheckDetails::Rationalize(bool asc) {
1487  bool found_useful_op = false;
1488  const uint32_t char_mask = CharMask(asc);
1489  mask_ = 0;
1490  value_ = 0;
1491  int char_shift = 0;
1492  for (int i = 0; i < characters_; i++) {
1493  Position* pos = &positions_[i];
1494  if ((pos->mask & String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) != 0) {
1495  found_useful_op = true;
1496  }
1497  mask_ |= (pos->mask & char_mask) << char_shift;
1498  value_ |= (pos->value & char_mask) << char_shift;
1499  char_shift += asc ? 8 : 16;
1500  }
1501  return found_useful_op;
1502 }

1526 EatsAtLeastInfo LoopChoiceNode::EatsAtLeastFromLoopEntry() {
1527  DCHECK_EQ(alternatives_->length(), 2); // There's just loop and continue.
1528 
1529  if (read_backward()) {
1530  // The eats_at_least value is not used if reading backward. The
1531  // EatsAtLeastPropagator should've zeroed it as well.
1532  DCHECK_EQ(eats_at_least_info()->eats_at_least_from_possibly_start, 0);
1533  DCHECK_EQ(eats_at_least_info()->eats_at_least_from_not_start, 0);
1534  return {};
1535  }
1536 
1537  // Figure out how much the loop body itself eats, not including anything in
1538  // the continuation case. In general, the nodes in the loop body should report
1539  // that they eat at least the number eaten by the continuation node, since any
1540  // successful match in the loop body must also include the continuation node.
1541  // However, in some cases involving positive lookaround, the loop body under-
1542  // reports its appetite, so use saturated math here to avoid negative numbers.
1543  // For this to work correctly, we explicitly need to use signed integers here.
1544  uint8_t loop_body_from_not_start = base::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(
1545  static_cast<int>(loop_node_->EatsAtLeast(true)) -
1546  static_cast<int>(continue_node_->EatsAtLeast(true)));
1547  uint8_t loop_body_from_possibly_start = base::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(
1548  static_cast<int>(loop_node_->EatsAtLeast(false)) -
1549  static_cast<int>(continue_node_->EatsAtLeast(true)));
1550 
1551  // Limit the number of loop iterations to avoid overflow in subsequent steps.
1552  int loop_iterations = base::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(min_loop_iterations());
1553 
1554  EatsAtLeastInfo result;
1555  result.eats_at_least_from_not_start =
1556  base::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(loop_iterations * loop_body_from_not_start +
1557  continue_node_->EatsAtLeast(true));
1558  if (loop_iterations > 0 && loop_body_from_possibly_start > 0) {
1559  // First loop iteration eats at least one, so all subsequent iterations
1560  // and the after-loop chunk are guaranteed to not be at the start.
1561  result.eats_at_least_from_possibly_start = base::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(
1562  loop_body_from_possibly_start +
1563  (loop_iterations - 1) * loop_body_from_not_start +
1564  continue_node_->EatsAtLeast(true));
1565  } else {
1566  // Loop body might eat nothing, so only continue node contributes.
1567  result.eats_at_least_from_possibly_start =
1568  continue_node_->EatsAtLeast(false);
1569  }
1570  return result;
1571 }

1573 bool RegExpNode::EmitQuickCheck(RegExpCompiler* compiler,
1574  Trace* bounds_check_trace, Trace* trace,
1575  bool preload_has_checked_bounds,
1576  Label* on_possible_success,
1577  QuickCheckDetails* details,
1578  bool fall_through_on_failure,
1579  ChoiceNode* predecessor) {
1580  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(predecessor);
1581  if (details->characters() == 0) return false;
1582  GetQuickCheckDetails(details, compiler, 0,
1583  trace->at_start() == Trace::FALSE_VALUE);
1584  if (details->cannot_match()) return false;
1585  if (!details->Rationalize(compiler->one_byte())) return false;
1586  DCHECK(details->characters() == 1 ||
1587  compiler->macro_assembler()->CanReadUnaligned());
1588  uint32_t mask = details->mask();
1589  uint32_t value = details->value();
1590 
1591  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
1592 
1593  if (trace->characters_preloaded() != details->characters()) {
1594  DCHECK(trace->cp_offset() == bounds_check_trace->cp_offset());
1595  // The bounds check is performed using the minimum number of characters
1596  // any choice would eat, so if the bounds check fails, then none of the
1597  // choices can succeed, so we can just immediately backtrack, rather
1598  // than go to the next choice. The number of characters preloaded may be
1599  // less than the number used for the bounds check.
1600  int eats_at_least = predecessor->EatsAtLeast(
1601  bounds_check_trace->at_start() == Trace::FALSE_VALUE);
1602  DCHECK_GE(eats_at_least, details->characters());
1603  assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(
1604  trace->cp_offset(), bounds_check_trace->backtrack(),
1605  !preload_has_checked_bounds, details->characters(), eats_at_least);
1606  }
1607 
1608  bool need_mask = true;
1609 
1610  if (details->characters() == 1) {
1611  // If number of characters preloaded is 1 then we used a byte or 16 bit
1612  // load so the value is already masked down.
1613  const uint32_t char_mask = CharMask(compiler->one_byte());
1614  if ((mask & char_mask) == char_mask) need_mask = false;
1615  mask &= char_mask;
1616  } else {
1617  // For 2-character preloads in one-byte mode or 1-character preloads in
1618  // two-byte mode we also use a 16 bit load with zero extend.
1619  static const uint32_t kTwoByteMask = 0xFFFF;
1620  static const uint32_t kFourByteMask = 0xFFFFFFFF;
1621  if (details->characters() == 2 && compiler->one_byte()) {
1622  if ((mask & kTwoByteMask) == kTwoByteMask) need_mask = false;
1623  } else if (details->characters() == 1 && !compiler->one_byte()) {
1624  if ((mask & kTwoByteMask) == kTwoByteMask) need_mask = false;
1625  } else {
1626  if (mask == kFourByteMask) need_mask = false;
1627  }
1628  }
1629 
1630  if (fall_through_on_failure) {
1631  if (need_mask) {
1632  assembler->CheckCharacterAfterAnd(value, mask, on_possible_success);
1633  } else {
1634  assembler->CheckCharacter(value, on_possible_success);
1635  }
1636  } else {
1637  if (need_mask) {
1638  assembler->CheckNotCharacterAfterAnd(value, mask, trace->backtrack());
1639  } else {
1640  assembler->CheckNotCharacter(value, trace->backtrack());
1641  }
1642  }
1643  return true;
1644 }
1645 
1646 // Here is the meat of GetQuickCheckDetails (see also the comment on the
1647 // super-class in the .h file).
1648 //
1649 // We iterate along the text object, building up for each character a
1650 // mask and value that can be used to test for a quick failure to match.
1651 // The masks and values for the positions will be combined into a single
1652 // machine word for the current character width in order to be used in
1653 // generating a quick check.
1654 void TextNode::GetQuickCheckDetails(QuickCheckDetails* details,
1655  RegExpCompiler* compiler,
1656  int characters_filled_in,
1657  bool not_at_start) {
1658  // Do not collect any quick check details if the text node reads backward,
1659  // since it reads in the opposite direction than we use for quick checks.
1660  if (read_backward()) return;
1661  Isolate* isolate = compiler->macro_assembler()->isolate();
1662  DCHECK(characters_filled_in < details->characters());
1663  int characters = details->characters();
1664  const uint32_t char_mask = CharMask(compiler->one_byte());
1665  for (int k = 0; k < elements()->length(); k++) {
1666  TextElement elm = elements()->at(k);
1667  if (elm.text_type() == TextElement::ATOM) {
1668  base::Vector<const base::uc16> quarks = elm.atom()->data();
1669  for (int i = 0; i < characters && i < quarks.length(); i++) {
1670  QuickCheckDetails::Position* pos =
1671  details->positions(characters_filled_in);
1672  base::uc16 c = quarks[i];
1673  if (IsIgnoreCase(compiler->flags())) {
1674  unibrow::uchar chars[4];
1675  int length =
1676  GetCaseIndependentLetters(isolate, c, compiler, chars, 4);
1677  if (length == 0) {
1678  // This can happen because all case variants are non-Latin1, but we
1679  // know the input is Latin1.
1680  details->set_cannot_match();
1681  pos->determines_perfectly = false;
1682  return;
1683  }
1684  if (length == 1) {
1685  // This letter has no case equivalents, so it's nice and simple
1686  // and the mask-compare will determine definitely whether we have
1687  // a match at this character position.
1688  pos->mask = char_mask;
1689  pos->value = chars[0];
1690  pos->determines_perfectly = true;
1691  } else {
1692  uint32_t common_bits = char_mask;
1693  uint32_t bits = chars[0];
1694  for (int j = 1; j < length; j++) {
1695  uint32_t differing_bits = ((chars[j] & common_bits) ^ bits);
1696  common_bits ^= differing_bits;
1697  bits &= common_bits;
1698  }
1699  // If length is 2 and common bits has only one zero in it then
1700  // our mask and compare instruction will determine definitely
1701  // whether we have a match at this character position. Otherwise
1702  // it can only be an approximate check.
1703  uint32_t one_zero = (common_bits | ~char_mask);
1704  if (length == 2 && ((~one_zero) & ((~one_zero) - 1)) == 0) {
1705  pos->determines_perfectly = true;
1706  }
1707  pos->mask = common_bits;
1708  pos->value = bits;
1709  }
1710  } else {
1711  // Don't ignore case. Nice simple case where the mask-compare will
1712  // determine definitely whether we have a match at this character
1713  // position.
1714  if (c > char_mask) {
1715  details->set_cannot_match();
1716  pos->determines_perfectly = false;
1717  return;
1718  }
1719  pos->mask = char_mask;
1720  pos->value = c;
1721  pos->determines_perfectly = true;
1722  }
1723  characters_filled_in++;
1724  DCHECK(characters_filled_in <= details->characters());
1725  if (characters_filled_in == details->characters()) {
1726  return;
1727  }
1728  }
1729  } else {
1730  QuickCheckDetails::Position* pos =
1731  details->positions(characters_filled_in);
1732  RegExpClassRanges* tree = elm.class_ranges();
1733  ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges = tree->ranges(zone());
1734  if (tree->is_negated() || ranges->is_empty()) {
1735  // A quick check uses multi-character mask and compare. There is no
1736  // useful way to incorporate a negative char class into this scheme
1737  // so we just conservatively create a mask and value that will always
1738  // succeed.
1739  // Likewise for empty ranges (empty ranges can occur e.g. when
1740  // compiling for one-byte subjects and impossible (non-one-byte) ranges
1741  // have been removed).
1742  pos->mask = 0;
1743  pos->value = 0;
1744  } else {
1745  int first_range = 0;
1746  while (ranges->at(first_range).from() > char_mask) {
1747  first_range++;
1748  if (first_range == ranges->length()) {
1749  details->set_cannot_match();
1750  pos->determines_perfectly = false;
1751  return;
1752  }
1753  }
1754  CharacterRange range = ranges->at(first_range);
1755  const base::uc32 first_from = range.from();
1756  const base::uc32 first_to =
1757  (range.to() > char_mask) ? char_mask : range.to();
1758  const uint32_t differing_bits = (first_from ^ first_to);
1759  // A mask and compare is only perfect if the differing bits form a
1760  // number like 00011111 with one single block of trailing 1s.
1761  if ((differing_bits & (differing_bits + 1)) == 0 &&
1762  first_from + differing_bits == first_to) {
1763  pos->determines_perfectly = true;
1764  }
1765  uint32_t common_bits = ~SmearBitsRight(differing_bits);
1766  uint32_t bits = (first_from & common_bits);
1767  for (int i = first_range + 1; i < ranges->length(); i++) {
1768  range = ranges->at(i);
1769  const base::uc32 from = range.from();
1770  if (from > char_mask) continue;
1771  const base::uc32 to =
1772  (range.to() > char_mask) ? char_mask : range.to();
1773  // Here we are combining more ranges into the mask and compare
1774  // value. With each new range the mask becomes more sparse and
1775  // so the chances of a false positive rise. A character class
1776  // with multiple ranges is assumed never to be equivalent to a
1777  // mask and compare operation.
1778  pos->determines_perfectly = false;
1779  uint32_t new_common_bits = (from ^ to);
1780  new_common_bits = ~SmearBitsRight(new_common_bits);
1781  common_bits &= new_common_bits;
1782  bits &= new_common_bits;
1783  uint32_t new_differing_bits = (from & common_bits) ^ bits;
1784  common_bits ^= new_differing_bits;
1785  bits &= common_bits;
1786  }
1787  pos->mask = common_bits;
1788  pos->value = bits;
1789  }
1790  characters_filled_in++;
1791  DCHECK(characters_filled_in <= details->characters());
1792  if (characters_filled_in == details->characters()) return;
1793  }
1794  }
1795  DCHECK(characters_filled_in != details->characters());
1796  if (!details->cannot_match()) {
1797  on_success()->GetQuickCheckDetails(details, compiler, characters_filled_in,
1798  true);
1799  }
1800 }

1804  positions_[i].mask = 0;
1805  positions_[i].value = 0;
1806  positions_[i].determines_perfectly = false;

1811 void QuickCheckDetails::Advance(int by, bool one_byte) {
1812  if (by >= characters_ || by < 0) {
1813  DCHECK_IMPLIES(by < 0, characters_ == 0);
1814  Clear();
1815  return;
1816  }
1817  DCHECK_LE(characters_ - by, 4);
1818  DCHECK_LE(characters_, 4);
1819  for (int i = 0; i < characters_ - by; i++) {
1820  positions_[i] = positions_[by + i];
1821  }
1822  for (int i = characters_ - by; i < characters_; i++) {
1823  positions_[i].mask = 0;
1824  positions_[i].value = 0;
1825  positions_[i].determines_perfectly = false;
1826  }
1827  characters_ -= by;
1828  // We could change mask_ and value_ here but we would never advance unless
1829  // they had already been used in a check and they won't be used again because
1830  // it would gain us nothing. So there's no point.
1831 }

1833 void QuickCheckDetails::Merge(QuickCheckDetails* other, int from_index) {
1834  DCHECK(characters_ == other->characters_);
1835  if (other->cannot_match_) {
1836  return;
1837  }
1838  if (cannot_match_) {
1839  *this = *other;
1840  return;
1841  }
1842  for (int i = from_index; i < characters_; i++) {
1843  QuickCheckDetails::Position* pos = positions(i);
1844  QuickCheckDetails::Position* other_pos = other->positions(i);
1845  if (pos->mask != other_pos->mask || pos->value != other_pos->value ||
1846  !other_pos->determines_perfectly) {
1847  // Our mask-compare operation will be approximate unless we have the
1848  // exact same operation on both sides of the alternation.
1849  pos->determines_perfectly = false;
1850  }
1851  pos->mask &= other_pos->mask;
1852  pos->value &= pos->mask;
1853  other_pos->value &= pos->mask;
1854  uint32_t differing_bits = (pos->value ^ other_pos->value);
1855  pos->mask &= ~differing_bits;
1856  pos->value &= pos->mask;
1857  }
1858 }

1940 RegExpNode* TextNode::FilterOneByte(int depth, RegExpCompiler* compiler) {
1941  RegExpFlags flags = compiler->flags();
1942  if (info()->replacement_calculated) return replacement();
1943  if (depth < 0) return this;
1944  DCHECK(!info()->visited);
1945  VisitMarker marker(info());
1946  int element_count = elements()->length();
1947  for (int i = 0; i < element_count; i++) {
1948  TextElement elm = elements()->at(i);
1949  if (elm.text_type() == TextElement::ATOM) {
1950  base::Vector<const base::uc16> quarks = elm.atom()->data();
1951  for (int j = 0; j < quarks.length(); j++) {
1952  base::uc16 c = quarks[j];
1953  if (!IsIgnoreCase(flags)) {
1954  if (c > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) return set_replacement(nullptr);
1955  } else {
1956  unibrow::uchar chars[4];
1957  int length = GetCaseIndependentLetters(compiler->isolate(), c,
1958  compiler, chars, 4);
1959  if (length == 0 || chars[0] > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) {
1960  return set_replacement(nullptr);
1961  }
1962  }
1963  }
1964  } else {
1965  // A character class can also be impossible to match in one-byte mode.
1966  DCHECK(elm.text_type() == TextElement::CLASS_RANGES);
1967  RegExpClassRanges* cr = elm.class_ranges();
1968  ZoneList<CharacterRange>* ranges = cr->ranges(zone());
1969  CharacterRange::Canonicalize(ranges);
1970  // Now they are in order so we only need to look at the first.
1971  // If we are in non-Unicode case independent mode then we need
1972  // to be a bit careful here, because the character classes have
1973  // not been case-desugared yet, but there are characters and ranges
1974  // that can become Latin-1 when case is considered.
1975  int range_count = ranges->length();
1976  if (cr->is_negated()) {
1977  if (range_count != 0 && ranges->at(0).from() == 0 &&
1978  ranges->at(0).to() >= String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) {
1979  bool case_complications = !IsEitherUnicode(flags) &&
1980  IsIgnoreCase(flags) &&
1981  RangesContainLatin1Equivalents(ranges);
1982  if (!case_complications) {
1983  return set_replacement(nullptr);
1984  }
1985  }
1986  } else {
1987  if (range_count == 0 ||
1988  ranges->at(0).from() > String::kMaxOneByteCharCode) {
1989  bool case_complications = !IsEitherUnicode(flags) &&
1990  IsIgnoreCase(flags) &&
1991  RangesContainLatin1Equivalents(ranges);
1992  if (!case_complications) {
1993  return set_replacement(nullptr);
1994  }
1995  }
1996  }
1997  }
1998  }
1999  return FilterSuccessor(depth - 1, compiler);
2000 }

2002 RegExpNode* LoopChoiceNode::FilterOneByte(int depth, RegExpCompiler* compiler) {
2003  if (info()->replacement_calculated) return replacement();
2004  if (depth < 0) return this;
2005  if (info()->visited) return this;
2006  {
2007  VisitMarker marker(info());
2008 
2009  RegExpNode* continue_replacement =
2010  continue_node_->FilterOneByte(depth - 1, compiler);
2011  // If we can't continue after the loop then there is no sense in doing the
2012  // loop.

2019 RegExpNode* ChoiceNode::FilterOneByte(int depth, RegExpCompiler* compiler) {
2020  if (info()->replacement_calculated) return replacement();
2021  if (depth < 0) return this;
2022  if (info()->visited) return this;
2023  VisitMarker marker(info());
2024  int choice_count = alternatives_->length();
2025 
2026  for (int i = 0; i < choice_count; i++) {
2027  GuardedAlternative alternative = alternatives_->at(i);
2028  if (alternative.guards() != nullptr &&
2029  alternative.guards()->length() != 0) {
2030  set_replacement(this);
2031  return this;
2032  }
2033  }
2034 
2035  int surviving = 0;
2036  RegExpNode* survivor = nullptr;
2037  for (int i = 0; i < choice_count; i++) {
2038  GuardedAlternative alternative = alternatives_->at(i);
2039  RegExpNode* replacement =
2040  alternative.node()->FilterOneByte(depth - 1, compiler);
2041  DCHECK(replacement != this); // No missing EMPTY_MATCH_CHECK.
2042  if (replacement != nullptr) {
2043  alternatives_->at(i).set_node(replacement);
2044  surviving++;
2045  survivor = replacement;
2046  }
2047  }
2048  if (surviving < 2) return set_replacement(survivor);
2049 
2050  set_replacement(this);
2051  if (surviving == choice_count) {
2052  return this;
2053  }
2054  // Only some of the nodes survived the filtering. We need to rebuild the
2055  // alternatives list.
2056  ZoneList<GuardedAlternative>* new_alternatives =
2057  zone()->New<ZoneList<GuardedAlternative>>(surviving, zone());
2058  for (int i = 0; i < choice_count; i++) {
2059  RegExpNode* replacement =
2060  alternatives_->at(i).node()->FilterOneByte(depth - 1, compiler);
2061  if (replacement != nullptr) {
2062  alternatives_->at(i).set_node(replacement);
2063  new_alternatives->Add(alternatives_->at(i), zone());
2064  }
2065  }
2066  alternatives_ = new_alternatives;
2067  return this;
2068 }

2070 RegExpNode* NegativeLookaroundChoiceNode::FilterOneByte(
2071  int depth, RegExpCompiler* compiler) {
2072  if (info()->replacement_calculated) return replacement();
2073  if (depth < 0) return this;

2092 void LoopChoiceNode::GetQuickCheckDetails(QuickCheckDetails* details,
2093  RegExpCompiler* compiler,
2094  int characters_filled_in,
2095  bool not_at_start) {
2096  if (body_can_be_zero_length_ || info()->visited) return;
2097  not_at_start = not_at_start || this->not_at_start();
2098  DCHECK_EQ(alternatives_->length(), 2); // There's just loop and continue.
2099  if (traversed_loop_initialization_node_ && min_loop_iterations_ > 0 &&
2100  loop_node_->EatsAtLeast(not_at_start) >
2101  continue_node_->EatsAtLeast(true)) {
2102  // Loop body is guaranteed to execute at least once, and consume characters
2103  // when it does, meaning the only possible quick checks from this point
2104  // begin with the loop body. We may recursively visit this LoopChoiceNode,
2105  // but we temporarily decrease its minimum iteration counter so we know when
2106  // to check the continue case.
2107  IterationDecrementer next_iteration(this);
2108  loop_node_->GetQuickCheckDetails(details, compiler, characters_filled_in,
2109  not_at_start);
2110  } else {
2111  // Might not consume anything in the loop body, so treat it like a normal
2112  // ChoiceNode (and don't recursively visit this node again).
2113  VisitMarker marker(info());
2114  ChoiceNode::GetQuickCheckDetails(details, compiler, characters_filled_in,
2115  not_at_start);
2116  }
2117 }

2119 void LoopChoiceNode::GetQuickCheckDetailsFromLoopEntry(
2120  QuickCheckDetails* details, RegExpCompiler* compiler,
2121  int characters_filled_in, bool not_at_start) {
2122  if (traversed_loop_initialization_node_) {
2123  // We already entered this loop once, exited via its continuation node, and
2124  // followed an outer loop's back-edge to before the loop entry point. We
2125  // could try to reset the minimum iteration count to its starting value at
2126  // this point, but that seems like more trouble than it's worth. It's safe
2127  // to keep going with the current (possibly reduced) minimum iteration
2128  // count.
2129  GetQuickCheckDetails(details, compiler, characters_filled_in, not_at_start);
2130  } else {
2131  // We are entering a loop via its counter initialization action, meaning we
2132  // are guaranteed to run the loop body at least some minimum number of times
2133  // before running the continuation node. Set a flag so that this node knows
2134  // (now and any times we visit it again recursively) that it was entered
2135  // from the top.
2136  LoopInitializationMarker marker(this);
2137  GetQuickCheckDetails(details, compiler, characters_filled_in, not_at_start);
2138  }

2173 // Check for [0-9A-Z_a-z].
2174 void EmitWordCheck(RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler, Label* word,
2175  Label* non_word, bool fall_through_on_word) {
2176  if (assembler->CheckSpecialClassRanges(
2177  fall_through_on_word ? StandardCharacterSet::kWord
2178  : StandardCharacterSet::kNotWord,
2179  fall_through_on_word ? non_word : word)) {
2180  // Optimized implementation available.
2181  return;
2182  }
2183  assembler->CheckCharacterGT('z', non_word);
2184  assembler->CheckCharacterLT('0', non_word);
2185  assembler->CheckCharacterGT('a' - 1, word);
2186  assembler->CheckCharacterLT('9' + 1, word);
2187  assembler->CheckCharacterLT('A', non_word);
2188  assembler->CheckCharacterLT('Z' + 1, word);
2189  if (fall_through_on_word) {
2190  assembler->CheckNotCharacter('_', non_word);
2191  } else {
2192  assembler->CheckCharacter('_', word);
2193  }
2194 }

2196 // Emit the code to check for a ^ in multiline mode (1-character lookbehind
2197 // that matches newline or the start of input).
2198 void EmitHat(RegExpCompiler* compiler, RegExpNode* on_success, Trace* trace) {
2199  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
2200 
2201  // We will load the previous character into the current character register.
2202  Trace new_trace(*trace);
2203  new_trace.InvalidateCurrentCharacter();
2204 
2205  // A positive (> 0) cp_offset means we've already successfully matched a
2206  // non-empty-width part of the pattern, and thus cannot be at or before the
2207  // start of the subject string. We can thus skip both at-start and
2208  // bounds-checks when loading the one-character lookbehind.
2209  const bool may_be_at_or_before_subject_string_start =
2210  new_trace.cp_offset() <= 0;
2211 
2212  Label ok;
2213  if (may_be_at_or_before_subject_string_start) {
2214  // The start of input counts as a newline in this context, so skip to ok if
2215  // we are at the start.
2216  assembler->CheckAtStart(new_trace.cp_offset(), &ok);
2217  }
2218 
2219  // If we've already checked that we are not at the start of input, it's okay
2220  // to load the previous character without bounds checks.
2221  const bool can_skip_bounds_check = !may_be_at_or_before_subject_string_start;
2222  assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(new_trace.cp_offset() - 1,
2223  new_trace.backtrack(), can_skip_bounds_check);
2224  if (!assembler->CheckSpecialClassRanges(StandardCharacterSet::kLineTerminator,
2225  new_trace.backtrack())) {
2226  // Newline means \n, \r, 0x2028 or 0x2029.
2227  if (!compiler->one_byte()) {
2228  assembler->CheckCharacterAfterAnd(0x2028, 0xFFFE, &ok);
2229  }
2230  assembler->CheckCharacter('\n', &ok);
2231  assembler->CheckNotCharacter('\r', new_trace.backtrack());
2232  }
2233  assembler->Bind(&ok);
2234  on_success->Emit(compiler, &new_trace);
2235 }

2239 // Emit the code to handle \b and \B (word-boundary or non-word-boundary).
2240 void AssertionNode::EmitBoundaryCheck(RegExpCompiler* compiler, Trace* trace) {
2241  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
2242  Isolate* isolate = assembler->isolate();
2243  Trace::TriBool next_is_word_character = Trace::UNKNOWN;
2244  bool not_at_start = (trace->at_start() == Trace::FALSE_VALUE);
2245  BoyerMooreLookahead* lookahead = bm_info(not_at_start);
2246  if (lookahead == nullptr) {
2247  int eats_at_least =
2248  std::min(kMaxLookaheadForBoyerMoore, EatsAtLeast(not_at_start));
2249  if (eats_at_least >= 1) {

2251  zone()->New<BoyerMooreLookahead>(eats_at_least, compiler, zone());
2252  FillInBMInfo(isolate, 0, kRecursionBudget, bm, not_at_start);
2253  if (bm->at(0)->is_non_word()) next_is_word_character = Trace::FALSE_VALUE;
2254  if (bm->at(0)->is_word()) next_is_word_character = Trace::TRUE_VALUE;
2255  }
2256  } else {
2257  if (lookahead->at(0)->is_non_word())
2258  next_is_word_character = Trace::FALSE_VALUE;
2259  if (lookahead->at(0)->is_word()) next_is_word_character = Trace::TRUE_VALUE;
2260  }
2261  bool at_boundary = (assertion_type_ == AssertionNode::AT_BOUNDARY);
2262  if (next_is_word_character == Trace::UNKNOWN) {
2263  Label before_non_word;
2264  Label before_word;
2265  if (trace->characters_preloaded() != 1) {
2266  assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(trace->cp_offset(), &before_non_word);
2267  }
2268  // Fall through on non-word.
2269  EmitWordCheck(assembler, &before_word, &before_non_word, false);
2270  // Next character is not a word character.
2271  assembler->Bind(&before_non_word);

2274  assembler->GoTo(&ok);
2275 
2276  assembler->Bind(&before_word);
2277  BacktrackIfPrevious(compiler, trace, at_boundary ? kIsWord : kIsNonWord);
2278  assembler->Bind(&ok);
2279  } else if (next_is_word_character == Trace::TRUE_VALUE) {
2280  BacktrackIfPrevious(compiler, trace, at_boundary ? kIsWord : kIsNonWord);
2281  } else {
2282  DCHECK(next_is_word_character == Trace::FALSE_VALUE);
2283  BacktrackIfPrevious(compiler, trace, at_boundary ? kIsNonWord : kIsWord);
2284  }
2285 }
2286 
2287 void AssertionNode::BacktrackIfPrevious(
2288  RegExpCompiler* compiler, Trace* trace,
2289  AssertionNode::IfPrevious backtrack_if_previous) {
2290  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
2291  Trace new_trace(*trace);
2292  new_trace.InvalidateCurrentCharacter();
2293 
2294  Label fall_through;
2295  Label* non_word = backtrack_if_previous == kIsNonWord ? new_trace.backtrack()
2296  : &fall_through;
2297  Label* word = backtrack_if_previous == kIsNonWord ? &fall_through
2298  : new_trace.backtrack();
2299 
2300  // A positive (> 0) cp_offset means we've already successfully matched a
2301  // non-empty-width part of the pattern, and thus cannot be at or before the
2302  // start of the subject string. We can thus skip both at-start and
2303  // bounds-checks when loading the one-character lookbehind.
2304  const bool may_be_at_or_before_subject_string_start =
2305  new_trace.cp_offset() <= 0;
2306 
2307  if (may_be_at_or_before_subject_string_start) {
2308  // The start of input counts as a non-word character, so the question is
2309  // decided if we are at the start.
2310  assembler->CheckAtStart(new_trace.cp_offset(), non_word);
2311  }
2312 
2313  // If we've already checked that we are not at the start of input, it's okay
2314  // to load the previous character without bounds checks.
2315  const bool can_skip_bounds_check = !may_be_at_or_before_subject_string_start;
2316  assembler->LoadCurrentCharacter(new_trace.cp_offset() - 1, non_word,
2317  can_skip_bounds_check);
2318  EmitWordCheck(assembler, word, non_word, backtrack_if_previous == kIsNonWord);
2319 
2320  assembler->Bind(&fall_through);
2321  on_success()->Emit(compiler, &new_trace);
2322 }

2335 void AssertionNode::Emit(RegExpCompiler* compiler, Trace* trace) {
2336  RegExpMacroAssembler* assembler = compiler->macro_assembler();
2337  switch (assertion_type_) {
2338  case AT_END: {
2339  Label ok;
2340  assembler->CheckPosition(trace->cp_offset(), &ok);
2341  assembler->GoTo(trace->backtrack());
2342  assembler->Bind(&ok);
2343  break;
2344  }
2345  case AT_START: {
2346  if (trace->at_start() == Trace::FALSE_VALUE) {
2347  assembler->GoTo(trace->backtrack());
2348  return;
2349  }
2350  if (trace->at_start() == Trace::UNKNOWN) {
2351  assembler->CheckNotAtStart(trace->cp_offset(), trace->backtrack());
2352  Trace at_start_trace = *trace;
2353  at_start_trace.set_at_start(Trace::TRUE_VALUE);
2354  on_success()->Emit(compiler, &at_start_trace);
2355  return;
2356  }
2357  } break;
2358  case AFTER_NEWLINE:
2359  EmitHat(compiler, on_success(), trace);
2360  return;
2361  case AT_BOUNDARY:
2362  case AT_NON_BOUNDARY: {
2363  EmitBoundaryCheck(compiler, trace);
2364  return;
2365  }
2366  }
2367  on_success()->Emit(compiler, trace);
2368 }
